                        'A delightful and tastefully presented 2 bed end stone cottage nicely positioned within a lovely area and with good sized rear garden adjoining open countryside. Lounge with feature fire. Modern dining kitchen and bath/ shower/ wc. Car parking. Viewing recommended //n//nOccupying a delightful position within a highly regarded part of the village this lovely, end stone cottage offers both well presented accommodation and a great garden and is certainly viewing to fully appreciate. //n//nThe property has a number of attractive qualities to very comfortable accommodation which includes an enclosed porch, lounge with feature fireplace, modern dining kitchen, rear porch and utility room. //n//nTo the first floor there are two double bedrooms and a neat bath/ shower/ wc. The property has gas fired central heating. //n//nOutside, directly to the rear there is a private courtyard area and two storage outhouses. There is car parking and a lovely garden adjoining open countryside.//n//nACCOMMODATION COMPRISES://n//nGROUND FLOOR//n//nEntrance Porch//nLounge 15\' 9" x 11\' 11" (4.80m x 3.35m)//nDining Kitchen 12\' 4" x 9\' 0" (3.76m x 2.74m)//nRear Porch//nUtility Room//n//nFIRST FLOOR//n//nLanding//nBedroom One (Front) 12\' 4" x 11\' 10" (3.76m x 3.60m)//nBedroom Two (Rear) 12\' 5" x 9\' 1" (3.76m x 2.77m)//nBath/Shower/WC//n//nOUTSIDE//n//nRear Courtyard//nStorage Outhouses//nCarparking//nDelightful Rear Garden //n//n//nFURTHER INFORMATION://n//nEPC: D (57)//nCOUNCIL TAX BAND: D',
                        'BEST & FINAL OFFERS TO BE RECEIVED BY FRIDAY 5TH AUGUST AT 12PM. Sure to prove a popular choice in the current market, this extensively & sympathetically modernised stone cottage is beautifully finished to an extremely high standard and is an opportunity not to be missed. Enjoying a country setting but close to the thriving village, viewing is essential to fully appreciate. Providing accommodation which includes a high quality \'heritage grey\' fitted kitchen, stunning classical style bath/shower/wc, lounge with feature fireplace, separate dining room, porch, rear lobby and storm porch, utility room, two good bedrooms ( one with robes ), useful car parking, detached garage, lovely gardens of good size and adjoining countryside. New boiler 2021 and upgraded electrics.//n//nSure to prove a popular choice in the current market, this extensively and sympathetically modernised stone cottage is beautifully finished to an extremely high standard and is an opportunity not to be missed.//n//nThe property occupies a lovely country setting within easy distance of the thriving village and viewing is essential to fully appreciate its many qualities.//n//nThe property is well designed and in brief features accommodation which includes to the ground floor of an entrance porch, comfortable lounge with attractive stone feature fireplace, there is a separate dining room with useful under stairs storage and a newly fitted kitchen with high quality \'herritage grey\' units and complementary wall tiling.//n//nThere is a rear vestibule/cloaks area and outside storm porch.  There is a stunning classical style bath/shower/wc complete with roll top claw foot bath and separate shower enclosure and finished with distinctive flooring.//n//nTo the first floor, there are two bedrooms, the main one of which has a cast iron fireplace and the second bedroom has built-in wardrobes.//n//nThe property has gas fired central heating and a new boiler was fitted in 2021 and the electrics have also been upgraded.//n//nOutside there is a pleasant stone flagged courtyard and a useful utility room.  There is good parking and a detached garage and well established gardens, the rear in particular being of an excellent size with lawn, rockery bed and views out over the countryside.//n//nNo onward chain.//n//nACCOMMODATION COMPRISES://n//nGROUND FLOOR//n//nEnclosed Porch//nLounge  13\' 0" + stair width x 12\' 0" (3.96m x 3.66m)//nSeparate Dining Room  11\' 8" x 8\' 11" (3.56m x 2.72m)//nNewly Fitted Modern Kitchen  11\' 10" x 8\' 1" (3.61m x 2.46m)//nInner Hall//nSide Porch//nBath/Shower/WC//nUtility Room\xa0 8\' 1" x 4\' 10" (2.46m x 1.47m)//n//nFIRST FLOOR//n//nLanding\xa0//nBedroom One (Rear)\xa0 12\' 5" x 10\' 2" (3.78m x 3.10m)//nBedroom Two (Front)\xa0 11\' 8" x 7\' 11" (3.56m x 2.41m)//n//nOUTSIDE//n//nDriveway Parking\xa0//nDetached Brick Built Garage\xa0 23\' 11" x 9\' 10" (7.29m x 3.00m)//nGardens//n//n//n//nFURTHER INFORMATION://n//nEPC: D//nCOUNCIL TAX BAND: D//nTENURE: Freehold',
                        '- This STUNNING EDWARDIAN SEMI DETACHED PERIOD HOME is BEAUTIFULLY APPOINTED throughout with a subtle Scandinavian influence resulting in light spacious rooms with a contemporary feel combined with attractive features expected of a property from its era. This home enjoys a SUPERB SEMI RURAL LOCATION close to delightful countryside yet with a wide range of amenities in Poynton being equally accessible. The current owners have upgraded and enhanced the accommodation in a variety of ways including herringbone style flooring, stylish fitted furniture and a sleek DINING KITCHEN with a range of integrated appliances.//n//n- The attention to detail shown by the current owners of this fantastic home is impressive and will be appreciated by anyone looking for a TURN KEY period property. There are 2 RECEPTION ROOMS both featuring WOODBURNERS complimenting the herringbone style flooring & providing attractive focal points. The LOUNGE is situated to the front while the SITTING ROOM has had double doors installed which open to the rear, there is also a deep storage area and even a doggy den! The property has been EXTENDED at ground floor level housing the super STYLISH DINING KITCHEN with attractive dark grey units, contrasting work tops and a range of high spec integrated `Bosch` appliances. A bespoke seating area has been installed with clever storage capacity.//n    //n- To the 1ST FLOOR there are 2 DOUBLE BEDROOMS and a CONTEMPORARY FAMILY BATHROOM. The main bedroom has the benefit of tall built in wardrobes to one wall, while the second bedroom has built in storage and enjoys pleasant views overlooking the rear garden. The bathroom has been appointed with an attractive modern white suite continuing the elegant & sophisticated theme which runs throughout this impressive home.//n//n- OUTSIDE, there is a smart grey block paved DRIVEWAY to the front with boundary hedging and brick walling. The REAR GARDEN is delightful with a pleasant hard landscaped seating area based around the rendered extension, and then a good sized lawned garden. At the top of the garden is a SUMMER HOUSE with power and has been utilised as a garden office as well as a useful storage facility. //n//n- Viewing is essential to appreciate the wonderful location and standard of accommodation this period home offers.//n//n- There is GAS FIRED HEATING & UPVC DOUBLE GLAZING.//n//n//n**PLEASE NOTE: The Tenure information shown has been taken from the official Land Registry Portal:   //n//nIf the Tenure is showing as "UNKNOWN" this means the information relating to the Tenure is not currently available on the official Land Registry Portal and we therefore advise you speak with your solicitor or take legal advice before viewing/offering/or committing to purchase this property IF the Tenure noted or lack of information affects you.//n//nIf the Tenure is shown as "FREEHOLD" or "LEASEHOLD" then this information was recorded when the property was made available and obtained from the Land Registry Portal. We cannot guarantee the information is accurate or up to date, however we expect it to be so, as it is the official register. Also to note: **All tenure types including Freehold, might have associated Rents payable. If you have any concerns you can email us on   before committing to view or offer.//n//n<b>what3words /// </b> chats.whistling.afterglow//n//n<b>Notice</b>//nPlease note we have not tested any appliances, including gas, electric, heating, water, showers, lights, boilers etc. We recommend if you have a particular concern, you consult a professional who is qualified in inspecting the type of appliance you are concerned about. Measurements are approximate and could change if a vendor has altered the property and failed to inform us of the change.',
